component.name: DjangoConsoleOptions

option.name: myCustomStartScript

task.summary:
Added an about page and a title to the index page
The about page was added by adding about.html and modifying the views.py, urls.py files. The about page uses a simpler function call in the view rather than by class as were the other examples. Adding the page title by variable to the index was more complicated than expected. I ended up modifying the "context" of the view in order to add the page_title variable, which was then referenceable in the index.html file.

Added a unittest to check page title in the functional_tests.py file
This is a selenium based unittest that loads a chrome browser with a given url localhost:8000/polls and checks the title of the web page that loads. Have been unable to resolve a 503 error that occurs whenever browser.quit() is called. Not sure if this is a legit error in this case as it is not running a selenium grid.
Add lists app to the project and added an initial unit test
Added URL mapping that handles the polls and lists apps

Made lists its own Django app in site settings, updates urls and views
Now the mysite project has two applications: polls and lists. This had to be declared in the site settings.py for the templates path to be seen by the framework. urls and views were updated to flesh out lists to have a index.html and root mapping.

Added support for adding an item via a POST
Changes in views.py, index.html for lists. There was a bug in index.html where the input tag was missing its name attribute. The home_page(request) function in views.py is now returning a render with two variables, one being the page title, with the new one being the returned text from a POST from the item_text input control on the form.

Added an item model class along with tests and migrations
Added a helper function in functional_tests to check each row of the table for the passed text string. Added a item model via models.py. Ran migrations. Then verified new tests were passing.

Cleaned up functional tests and started adding LiveServerTestCase
Moved functional tests for both lists and polls sites into a \mysite_proj\ functional_test directory. Began working on LiveServerTestCase method to run functional tests, which will create a temporary data set for testing that is discarded after the test run.

Added a list.html page that will show per-user-ToDo lists
Added the html, refactored index.html, lists/tests.py, urls, views, and functional_tests to incorporate the new list.html.

Began wiring in the /lists/new action plus refactoring
Refactored out duplicate tests home_page_only_saves_items_when_. Added NewListTest and incorporated like home_page_can_save_POST, home_page_redirects_after_POST test cases there. Modified URLS.PY adding the new_list view. Added a new_list view to VIEWS.PY.

Added a List into the model, updated view and tests
Introduced the List into the models. Updated tests to be aware of and test for the new List model. Migrations for the new model.

Enable adding items to individual lists
Added a new view "add_item", updated view_list to accept a list_id in parameter, then to filter and render that list. Modified URLS.PY to accept an add_item URL and updated to search explicitly for numbers in the URL path (not as greedy). Added NewItemTest test cases. Updated ListViewTest to see that only items for the given list are displayed and to see that the expected list is passed to the template. Updated LIST.HTML to incorporate receiving a list.id.
Changed mysite/urls to call an alias instead of namespace

Added bootstrap to files and refactored lists html with templates
Pulled the bootstrap version from the tutorial (3.3.4). Unzipped the files into the lists/static directory. Updated lists/index.html and lists/list.html, added base.html to add some blocks for header and form actions.

Make use of bootstrap stylesheets to modify index and lists.html
Added divs to base.html to use jumbotron class. Added a base.css file for overriding bootstrap. Changed to StaticLiveServerTestCase in order for CSS to load in the functional tests. Added table class tag in list.html.
